
[1]grateful

   GRA'TEFUL, a. [from L. gratus. See Grace.]

   1. Having a due sense of benefits; kindly disposed towards one from
   whom a favor has been received; willing to acknowledge and repay
   benefits; as a grateful heart.

   2. Agreeable; pleasing; acceptable; gratifying; as a grateful present;
   a grateful offering.

   3. Pleasing to the taste; delicious; affording pleasure; as food or
   drink grateful offering.

   Now golden fruits on loaded branches shine,

   And grateful clusters swell with floods of wine.
